<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-1 Vector Operations and Applications</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete both problems. To earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        problem 2 and one part of problem 1.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>Let <m>\vec{u}=\langle 5,-1,3\rangle, \vec{v}=\langle 1,-2,2\rangle,</m> 
            and <m>\vec{w}=\langle 2,4,0\rangle</m></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find <m>\vec{v}\cdot(\vec{u}\times\vec{w})</m></p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the vector in the direction of <m>\vec{w}</m> with length of 
        <m>2\vec{u}</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
      <statement><p>A triangular sail has vertices located at the spatial coordinates 
        P(1, 0, 0), Q(3, 2, 0), and R(1, 1, 4). Use the cross product of the displacement 
        vectors <m>\vec{PQ}</m> and <m>\vec{PR}</m> to calculate the exact surface area 
        of the sail.</p></statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>